shared_text:
Patrick Henry Elementary
August 19 at 1:52 PM ¬∑

Back to School Bash DRIVE-THRU is scheduled for Tuesday August 25th from 5:30 - 7:00. This is for grades Preschool and 1st - 4th (Kindergarten is excluded because they have their own orientations). Please use this map as a reference guide. It shows where teachers will be set up and where the nurse station is located. It also highlights appropriate routes while on campus. This is an excellent opportunity for you and your child to meet their teacher while remaining socially distanced. Families can also drop off their school supplies or any items that still need returned from last school year (i.e. Chromebooks and chargers, Library books, teacher books, etc.). Also, if your child receives medication at school, we will have a Nurse Station where you can drop off medications for our nursing staff to store at school. Please take advantage of this quick "meet and greet" with your child's teacher as we move closer to the start of the new school year. If you have specific questions, please contact bhieber@phpatriots.org.

United Way of Henry County
June 23 at 12:40 PM ¬∑

Reading Pledge for Your Recent Kindergarten Graduate!
20 minutes of reading a day is critical for children. Encourage and support your young reader this summer. United Way of Henry County wants to help inspire your reader and support local businesses throughout Henry County with a reading challenge. If you commit to have your child read 20 minutes a day for three weeks and celebrate your child‚Äôs accomplishment with a trip to a local business for an ice cream treat we will mail you the Elephant & Piggie book ‚ÄúShould I Share My Ice Cream‚Äù along with another book. Please message us through Facebook or e-mail tom@unitedwayhenry.org committing to the reading pledge, tell us who your child‚Äôs Kindergarten teacher was and give us your and your child‚Äôs name and mailing address. We will send your soon to be 1st grader the two books to kick off their summer reading!
We are grateful to the United Way donors and volunteers for making this possible.

text:
Our first meeting for a first summer workout will be held tomorrow Friday June 12, at 9:00 AM on the high school track. Please remember to avoid congregating, bring a towel and personal water bottle. Tomorrow's workout will include drills, an introduction to "Boot Camp" for some,and a short run 20 to 30 minutes. After the workout I will ask each runner to take home a uniform to try on. I expect to be finished by 10:30 AM.

Also. If you haven't done so already please read the OHSSA guidelines for sport before coming to the workout.

And sorry, but ICe cream Friday is on hold.

Coach Parry

Amanda Held is with Justin Held.
May 31 at 9:35 PM ¬∑

HAPPY BIRTHDAY PATRIOT!!! üéÇ üéÅ üç∞

A year ago this special little soul made his appearance into the world. At first glance we knew something about him was ‚Äúdifferent‚Äù. What we didn‚Äôt know is the gravity of how he would impact and inspire those around him.

We were criticized for keeping him alive. People thought that we should ‚Äúput him out of his misery‚Äù and that we were ‚Äúselfish and cruel for keeping him alive‚Äù.

There are many things I don‚Äôt know, but the one thing I DO know with all my might is that everything happens for a reason. And I know that every day with this little guy is a gift.

Congratulations on your first trip around the sun little buddy! And here‚Äôs to many more days of spreading hope and happiness to all you meet! üá±üá∑üíôüê¥

#patriottheminimini #differentisawesome #horsesofhooves

The following will be our Varsity Letter Policy for Spring 2020 and beyond during a pandemic like COVID 19.

*All Seniors will letter.

*All Returning Letterwinners will letter (as long as they intended on playing this year).

*All Underclassmen will letter retroactively if they letter the next year in the same sport. (Must be on eligibility roster both years).

***All students must be academically eligible and meet Athletic Handbook Code of Conduct expectations

***This policy will ensure that all seniors are recognized. ***This policy will ensure that all returning letter winners are recognized.

***This policy will allow underclassmen the opportunity to letter retroactively if they letter during the same sport in the next academic year.
